column1: 76032;instagram;2019-01-15 09:36:42;FALSE;"have you seen gillette’s new advert speaking out against toxic masculinity?  it starts a conversation around #metoo and asks men to stop harassing women – and each other.

i’m so pleased to see a traditionally male brand taking up the mantle and speaking up against harassment and abuse.  now we need other brands to follow suit and make better adverts along the same lines.  i don’t want to mention the corny acting – oops
column2: just did – but this is a gift too because it leaves room for other brands to find more creative ways to express the same message.

column4: it’s not just piers.  head over to twitter to check out how many men think gillette just launched a personal attack on them 🙄

column2: the messages here are going to trigger a lot of men.  why?  because it’s really easy to step aside and let men bully women
column4: but so much harder to look at your own behaviour and where you allow it to happen or perpetuate this yourself.

column1: there is so much work to do.

column1: 76049;instagram;2019-01-15 08:14:25;FALSE;"when @petey_gibson asked if i wanted to perform in a drag king show to benefit the film we’re in together(@thesympathycard)
soon after i realized i’d never actually performed in drag

column2: my wife @mzjillbennett is the reigning misster la / drag king champ (since the early aughts!) and gave me a vote of confidence.

column1: i watch a lot of @rupaulsdragrace & think about the gender politics of drag often (esp. about the difficulty of performing as a drag king simply because the act in and of itself doesn’t always scream “subversive!” the way it often does for queens).
all that to say i spent a lot of time thinking about what i’ve missed watching some drag king performances: is there more than crotch-grabbing
column3: trying desperately to cloak oneself in tropes and the privileges afforded the male gender? i’d like to avoid seeing or hearing or interacting with another douchey dude for the rest of my life if i can help it... so i couldn’t very well make it my goal to try to be one.

column2: since halloween 2017 i’ve been told my face is eerily reminiscent of prince
column3: so i figured i’d perform as him. “how would prince respond to the #metoo movement?” i thought. 🕺🏽

column1: and so i printed photos of a dozen muthafuckers accused and/or found guilty of sexual assault/abuse-misconduct
column2: put them in a “binder o’ lil bitches
column6: and tore them to shreds onstage. i attached photos of kavanaugh/weinstein/cosby to masks
column7: crossed out their faces with lipstick
column8: and slapped the shit out of them throughout the performance.

column2: why are we starting to see more and more deficiencies pop up in the sunshine state? how can we increase our levels? why on earth should we even bother?
the sunshine discussion is highly controversial at the moment and i don't want anything i say to be taken out of context (because that never happens on sm right!?) however
column3: if you tune into the latest episode we discuss some of the research around vitamin d and autoimmunity
column6: vitamin d and cardiovascular health etc. and we also dive into the recommendations put forward by the vitamin d council of australia around safe levels of sun exposure and how to correct deficiencies. #controversy 😜

column1: fyi: vitamin d is a fat soluble vitamin. the worst idea we ever came up with (ok
column2: there have been a lot of bad ideas in the nutrition world) was low fat food. all those gorgeous fat soluble vitamins.... rip.
with a lil full fat yoghurt lapping up a lil afternoon sunshine... well
column3: that's a pretty insanely awesome prescription right there!

column1: 76113;instagram;2019-01-15 07:21:37;FALSE;"no one can tell me what i can & cant say
i was built with an exterior that has battled the ugliest storms. but for my foundation to never crumble —
it’s my interior’s strength that isn’t like others 🌪🌪🌪
i dislike that i begin this by being defensive...
i believe people help people with stories like mine
i got big balls —  this is for those who feel alone .

column2: i felt pure happiness i never felt

column1: i was going to become a mom for the first time ♥️
today i’m full of deep breaths & sadness
a terrible loss happened last night .
i’ve learned at a very young age —
you cant control everything that happens to you
but you do control how you let it affect you! .
it’s no lie i wear my heart on my sleeve.. and i wear the things i have survived like badges of honor
the power of healing for me
column2: happens with helping others. i’m not afraid to stand up and say “ me too”

column1: or to say.. “ i lost the baby”. .
this badge is painful to put on my jacket 💔
but from this — will come new possibilities & loads of trust in the big man up stairs 🙏🏻 .
thank you for all the messages
♥️ my little family feels incredibly loved .
and for you — the woman i want to never feel alone. .
this pain has no words to describe
there’s no time line to make the loss hurt less .
keep your chin up! hold those positive thoughts close to your heart. remember that tomorrow is a brand new day. 🌻🌻each day is filled with infinite possibilities!!! 🌻🌻

not much of a physical change but i really wish i would have listened to my mother when she told me not to mess with my eyebrows ☹️ thank goodness that trend is over!
19 year old me hid away her feelings
column2: never dropped a tear in public and kept everything bottled up
column3: she was scared to speak up for herself
column4: the people she called friends abused of her kindness and took her for granted. she blamed herself for things that happened in her in past
column5: she lacked self-esteem and secretly cared of what others thought. she had gone through two suicide attempts and still wondered if life was worth living. she had never experienced heartbreak or even thought she was capable of loving someone. 19 year old me knew she needed help but wouldn't dare to seek it
column6: instead she would smile and hide all her pain.

column1: today i'm still a work in progress. i'm not perfect nor will i ever be
column2: i have my days and i accept my flaws. i no longer keep my mouth shut
column3: i don't care what others may think. i know my worth
column4: i love myself and all my curves. my happiness comes first before others
column5: it's okay to be selfish once in a while. i'm no longer shy to meet new people but i only trust the few that have stuck with me through thick and thin. i no longer blame myself for my past
column6: i now know that giving up is not the answer.

column1: everyone we meet is fighting a battle we know nothing of
column2: so be kind. i publicly share my story because i know i am not alone
column3: my story isn't over. don't be ashamed of what you've been through. be proud of what you've  overcome because you matter and you are worthy of love.

column1: i've had isolation on my mind a bunch lately. i lived in partial isolation while living a double life for about a decade. there was no social media normalizing being a stripper. no one got to see us as human beings with dynamic personalities & lives.

it felt easier to live isolated than to either deal with being hit with the stigma of sex work. it felt easier to live isolated than have to hear people warn me to ""be careful"" in an industry they know nothing but rumors about. it felt easier to isolate than to have to lie all the time. if i had a bad day at work
column3: ""well what do you expect?"" it was easier to not deal with society's small minds.

column1: i stopped caring what other people would think i felt so light & free!
i chose to be an exotic entertainer. i had options. i'm proud that i did it. i learned so much i wrote a book!
no one chooses to be a victim of sexual violence.
some victims of sexual violence end up living isolated
column2: even when in crowds of people
column3: for fear of the reactions of others.

column1: no one has to blame a victim of sexual violence
column2: we are doing it to ourselves. we obsessively try to figure out how we could have prevented it. the vitriol spewed whenever a case is big in the media solidifies that this choice was right. it shouldn't be this way.

column1: isolation led to me really coming to love & feel recharged by time alone. ""introverts unite separately at our homes!!!""

column2: the isolation is not a happy place to be. it is not self imposed. it is society imposed. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column1: i have had isolation on my mind a bunch lately. i lived in paial isolation while living a double life for about a decade. there was no social media normalizing being a stripper. no one got to see us as human beings with dynamic personalities & lives.

it felt easier to live isolated than to either deal with being hit with the stigma of sex work. it felt easier to live isolated than have to hear people warn me to ""be careful"" in an industry they know nothing but rumors about. it felt easier to isolate than to have to lie all the time. if i had a bad day at work
column3: ""well what do you expect?"" it was easier to not deal with society's small minds.

column1: women can be misogynists too. its how we learned to survive and defend ourselves in a world that felt often like a battlefield. i remember that meaning you were a down chick
column2: you could hold your own. but in relationships you let your guard down and that same dude would show you why you had it up in the first place. and the cycled continued. even the ""nice guys"" did shady abusive ish.

column1: im ashamed of the person i became because of abuse. i was violent and have been healing all that misogyny in so many ways. i was abusive to men (i use to defend that with what they did to me or others...but i can't anymore - i want to move on from that past). i did not make safe spaces for my sisters as much as i wish i could have and i was deep in addiction and self harm. detoxing the heteronormative white supremacist patriarchy isn't some ""fad"" also queerness isn't a "" trend"" its about getting healthy
column2: holding ourselves + other accountable and finally being able to be vulnerable
column5: create a better world together. (i am  thankful for my queer siblings for this - our voice is doing divine work on this planet and i see that)

column1: everyday i think about what i've done. i try to process
column6: community. there is so much guilt. im learning self-forgiveness and better boundaries. how to be gentle with me and how to go in and hold child-me
column7: tell them they are are so important and deserve to feel safe. and also demand accountability of myself.

column1: if you're reading this and we've had a difficult of fucked up interaction know that i am sorry. know that i am changing and growing and learning. i know it doesnt change the past
column3: but what i can offer is my contribution to a healthier future.

many come to yoga seeking answers to deep personal struggles
column3: and desperately needing a supportive community. this makes them prime targets for yoga cults which promise “a cure for every ill - naturally.” .

column2: like many sincere groups (spiritual or otherwise)
column7: a sense of worth and direction. but a cult will elevate its leaders
column9: and identity on a pedestal above critical accountability. .

column1: i was no different when i started. i had my own years of turmoil
column2: pain and mental health concoctions to sort through after severe depression and autoimmune disorder. i was insanely stressed out from pressures to work 60-70 hours weeks most of the year.

column1: yoga was a life saver at first - and then it slowly took over everything. .

i unwittingly joined the yoga cult. i soaked up everything. i renounced “my corporate life.” that was the “old me.” except the deeper i got... slowly the cracks in this “perfect new world” began to show. i realized some things just don’t add up. .
so i began to question. like “why are you charging $30 per student but paying teachers $25 a class and asking them to do 30 minutes of admin work before and after?” .
or “if your certification is so prestigious and top-quality
column2: why are medical professionals not recognizing its credence and validity?” .

column1: or “why am i paying someone thousands of dollars to tell me that i can’t make a full time living doing the job she’s supposed to train me to do?""
the yoga community will almost always respond to challengers through psychological manipulation
those who openly express doubt or dissent are shamed
column4: often publicly for their “aggressive and ego based tactics.”"" -@thebodyintuitive

76327;instagram;2019-01-15 02:09:54;FALSE;"ok i’ll hop in this challenge... 1st profile pic on fb vs now... a lot more has changed then it might appear... i’m still rockin big chains ⛓ still invited to everythang 😜
column3: but my minds a sky rocket 🚀 ... i’ve been grinding my ass off for a long time and finding my way into events in clubs to network before i was even old enough 🙈 i began to network across the country
column4: which led me to play in cities across the country
column5: in which i’ve been blessed to meet real friends and be accepted into life long neighborhoods that feel like my own when i come thru (shout out to my fam in oakland
column8: & reno ♥️🙏🏻♥️) although i have performed quite a bit
column9: i have so many unfinished or unreleased projects over the years that we’re out of my control
column10: which all are only a testiment to how difficult the journey has been for me. but life is about seasons. i’ve been sowing seeds for a looooong time. i’m finally at a place when things are coming into harvest and i am so excited to share my carefully grown crop with you all❣️2yrs ago i was featured in the book @thediaryofasongwriter and we recorded a soundtrack to it that made the #grammy ballots 🙌🏻 that was a major project for me which actually was pushing for light on this entire #metoo movement before #harveyweinstein was being discussed. shout out to someone i consider family @devineevans for being a man willing to stand up to this and doing such a beautiful project ♥️ in 2018 i released my first music video “zombies” and was blessed to have it nominated for “song of the year” at the #upstart awards! 🙏🏻 i also had over 60 shows last yr. then i joined forces with the beautiful @dvineesofine in becoming a duo known as the flintstoners (follow us!! 👉🏻@420flintstoners 👈🏽) and we released our 1st single “yabbadabbadoo” with the music video coming soon!🦖🦕

column1: 76360;instagram;2019-01-15 01:23:28;FALSE;"so this weekend i did a thing.  i completely stepped outside of my comfort zone and i attended the national conference in toronto.  you guys
column2: i was so scared.  one of my biggest fears is of being alone.  i was going to this convention alone and i had no idea what to expect.

column1: what if they don’t like me?
what if i have to awkwardly speak in front of them?  i spent countless nights restlessly trying to sleep while my mind was telling me every reason not to go. “you shouldn’t leave the kids
column2: what if something happens while you’re gone
column3: there’s so much work to do at home
column4: we don’t have the funds to go” .

column2: i woke up that morning and made my way. more anxiety appeared
column4: what if we get in an accident
column5: what if i get lost when i get there”. fast forward to making it (phew) to the hotel.  and you know what?  once i got there
column8: my fear and anxiety melted away.  i stopped worrying about all the things and i just embraced and enjoyed every moment and had the best weekend with some amazing and inspiring people.  i am still so blown away that i conquered this fear of mine but i also feel so proud of pushing myself outside of my “safe zone” and doing something different.  i have a long way to come with my anxiety
column9: but it was a step.  a step forward.  a step that i hope i can continue to do in the future and in my everyday life.

column1: anxiety can be so exhausting and frustrating hey?
so i have to stop and say thank you to usborne for pushing me outside of my comfort level
column2: thank you to all the girls that made me feel so welcome
column4: for being brave.  i did it.  and you know what?  you can too.

column1: it was so disturbing that i could not look away. @rkelly you are a despicable human being. your abuse towards these young women is so vile and 1000% unacceptable. we have to do something about it. we start small with conversations and simple things like committing to never playing your #music. we ask the same of our #dj and #radio hosts. we stop purchasing tickets to your shows or demand our money back if a collaborative event doesn’t take you off the performers list. we continue to listen to #survivors because their stories are powerful and impactful and remind us that there is an inherent abuse of power in so many industries. we will not keep quiet. we will not sit down. we will #standup. we will #speakout.

column1: 76376;instagram;2019-01-15 01:30:29;FALSE;"you showed us the sun in all its splendor and with the same love you raised the moon to glow with elegance. you are truly greatest! you are omni and your beauty is seen in all your creations. teach me oh creator to acknowledge and appreciate all of your beauty. also to keep my eyes open so i see you more if not always over seeing and focusing on my toughest circumstances. let me grow from them while focusing on you primarily. im not perfect yet you allowed me to see the sun set. my request to you almighty creator..is that you see me beyond my innocent and arrogant imperfections and instead see me for the love you placed in my heart that im so focused on trying to spread. thank you for mercy grace and wisdom. may the sun rise in my path in the morning hours and wisdom by my bedside so i walk more and more in righteousness each day. one who is powerful and mighty forever and always.. all praises to you omnipotent one. amen. let it be so.

column1: 76397;instagram;2019-01-15 00:46:11;FALSE;"here’s a sad story from a client:
___________________________________________ “my narcissistic ex tortures my children with passive aggressive comments
column2: silent treatments & rage. my daughter is particularly sensitive & anxious & she cannot function when she’s exposed to her father. but since she has cut him out of her life
column3: he has refused to financially or emotionally support her in even the smallest way. he makes roughly 10x what i make
column4: but he manipulates both my daughter & me by refusing to cover even basic expenses. still worse

column6: while simultaneously driving her further & further away from a real father/daughter relationship. he cannot grasp that being cruel & controlling to her will not make her love him. it is truly heartbreaking.” __________________________________________

column1: 76458;instagram;2019-01-14 21:40:52;FALSE;"i have one goal that has trumped all others for 2019 ... to eat more fruits and veggies.
despite the happy place i’m at with my exercise routine
column2: the healthy habit of veggies still feels like a chore
column3: you guys! am i the only one?

column1: i want this to change. for good. forever. i want to be someone who eats veggies. and not just over the next six weeks while i do this healthy habits challenge with @biceps.after.babies (although i am happy i have that to get the ball rolling) but forever. well into my old age! i’m working right now on creating a new habit! .

it was like amber had me in mind when she gave us our first weeks challenge; to incorporate one new fruit or veggie we haven’t had before ... each day! i am having so much fun with this! todays fruit? persimmon.
click on “recipes” on the link in my bio for this persimmon bread pudding recipe for two. it makes a wonderful dessert

column1: 76466;instagram;2019-01-14 23:24:00;FALSE;"⚠️ long caption ahead but it’s a love story

right before i met ean i was in a really dark place. i had just finished my first year of college and spent the majority of it hating myself. i had no self-worth and no love for the person i was. thinking i could just drink all my problems away
column2: i wound up in several situations where i was used
column4: and afraid. after awhile i just decided “this is who i am” “a nobody that people will use and a nobody that doesn’t deserve genuine love or compassion”. fast forward to today and i am a wife
column6: and dog mom. past traumas are still being worked through every single day but i wouldn’t have even considered that i am a person who deserves help without ean in my life. he has taken me around the world and given me experiences that have changed my life. traveling with my husband (who is also my best friend btw) has always been reassurance that i am a person of worth and that i do deserve this love. people may have really hurt me and taken advantage of me in my past in ways that requires a lot of healing
column7: but they did not break me. i am so blessed to be a 23 year old woman who has seen so much of this incredible world 🌎 💕";;en;;;;;;0;;eankatyadventures;Ean & Katy Adventures;;0;False;16;0;0;193;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/48801cb3168842ee465bfb974156ce42/5D28FB63/t51.2885-15/e35/49515993_331175427483217_4930090838436057727_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"⚠️ long caption ahead but it’s a love story

thing is maybe it’s none of our faults.
i used to think about you day and night like a little girl who’s anxious for it to be the next morning to find out what santa clause  had brought her.
i used to think about you kissing me all day.
now all i can think of is spending the rest of my time getting to know me and celebrating with friends
but i don’t think of you
all i can think of is me
and after me all i can think of is myself
i’m sorry that i no longer think of you
i’m sorry that i no longer dream of you
but importantly i’m sorry i no longer love

column1: 76527;instagram;2019-01-14 22:52:59;FALSE;"i have set up this page to help raise awareness of sexual harassment in the work place.

i was subjected to months of intermittent sexual harassment by my department director. i didn't feel i could report it and didn't know how to stop it. this led eventually to a count of sexual assault which i have no evidence or proof of. my employer did not believe my claims. i could no longer work there after this.
had i known anybody who could help me
column2: or anybody who had experienced a similar situation i might have been able to prevent the assault from happening. or at the very least i might have been able to gather the evidence i need to prove it to my employer.

column1: 76546;instagram;2019-01-14 22:01:55;FALSE;"is there such thing as an ethical sugar daddy?
first thing’s first: let’s define some terms. being a “sugar daddy” refers to a relationship in which one person provides some sort of financial benefit to the other
column2: who provides very little financially to the relationship. as far as relationship power dynamics go
so back to the question. can one become an ethical sugar daddy? this is a question one reader submitted to kristin wong
column3: who pens our new joint accounts financial advice column.

column1: the reader asks: “i’m a mid-30s gay man and i’ve finally arrived in my career to the point where i’m making decent money. i like taking lots of trips
column3: and drinking nice cocktails. i also want to share that with a boyfriend or lover. but often
column5: they’re less far along in their career and don’t make as much money. i’ve dabbled in the sugar-daddy dynamic a bit
column6: paying for everything we did together
column8: i kind of liked it. sometimes
column9: i want to do fancy things with a guy and i don’t want his financial situation to stop us. but with the #metoo movement and my awareness of how power and money influence a relationship
column10: how do i be an ethical sugar daddy? and how do i create the right boundaries so i also don’t get taken advantage of? how do i have these conversations with a partner?”

column1: intrigued? tap the link in our bio to read the response on joint accounts
column2: our new advice column at the intersection of money and relationships. and if you have a question of your own

76563;instagram;2019-01-14 22:11:54;FALSE;today about 400 new orleanians gathered to protest trump
column3: and the wall. we heard from different communities and their message was the same: an injury to one is an injury to all. one after the other clearly stated that this is a protest against trump but it was also a solidarity demo with the international working class. what is happening at the border is also happening in our communities. our people are under attack worldwide so it doesn’t start or end with trump. we must have an international/ anti imperialist movement if we want to be successful. that the shut down is an attack on workers and that we will not capitulate to racist amerikkka. we must keep fighting. truly inspirational! almost every speaker referenced katrina to remind folks that communities came together to rebuild together and that the work is feasible. that we need to organize and stop racism and fear mongering from dividing us
column4: the working class. el pueblo unido jamás será vencido

76568;instagram;2019-01-14 22:14:11;FALSE;our newest contributor [simply_kelby] shared this story with us today about how her best friend raped her. we’re so proud of her for breaking her silence. her story matters. read her story below 👇

column3: when my best friend raped me.

column1: it was a normal night hanging out with friends. we had been drinking a little and with my recent breakup with my fiancé
column2: i drank way more than i should have. i later found myself passed out on the floor.
my friends picked me up and put me to bed. one friend
column4: stayed behind letting everyone know that he would “take care of me” while everyone else went to the other room and watched a movie.

column1: he stayed in the room with me. i cannot tell you what he did as i was unconscious through all of it. one of my friends walked in while john was sexually assaulting me but thought it was consensual
column2: so he did nothing. when john was finished
column3: he walked out and left the apartment.

column2: my friends came into the bedroom to tell me what they thought i had done. it took them a few minutes to wake me and when they did
column3: they told me that i had had sex with john. i looked at them with fear in my eyes because i had no idea what they were talking about. i looked down and realized i wasn’t wearing any underwear and that i was wearing different shorts then when i had passed out. it was that moment that i realized something was not right
column4: and i had been raped by my best friend.

column2: my friends immediately called the police and a few of them went to john’s house to make sure he stayed there until the police arrived. while i was waiting on the police to show
column3: all i could think about was why me and how could my best friend betray me like this?

column1: it has taken me a very long time to heal from that night and honestly
column2: i am still working on it. trust does not come easily to me now because of him. it’s a constant reminder that sometimes you may think you know somebody but

column1: 76573;instagram;2019-01-14 22:18:07;FALSE;"i decided to enter 2019 with intention and purpose. i am using my social media platforms to share my art as i intended when creating them. i wrote this poem while reflecting on experiences others have shared with me of surviving abuse and assault. these conversations have often been hidden. in secret. in the way that many survivors have been taught to be silent.

i haven’t watched the #survivingrkelly docuseries. i’m being mindful of things that feel triggering. but i have heard the stories of the survivors over the years. i haven’t listened to his music since i was child. the truth has always been there. the docuseries hasn’t brought something to light that was hidden. but in this present moment it seems that society is waking up
column2: albeit slowly willing to listen. and this conversation needs to be had.

column1: because there are many who have harmed girls
column2: boys and women. many whom society has allowed to continue harming others or pass through life without any consequence of their actions. some are entertainers like r kelly
column3: some are religious leaders and some are family members. the list goes on. abusers exist in all types of spaces and are not confined to a gender

column1: this week i have been reflecting on the bravery of the survivors in the docuseries and the bravery that many hold inside.
there is an energy present right now: one of truth. and we all need to be a part of it. there are so many quiet warriors amongst us
column2: may we celebrate truth by having this conversation. may this conversation be had in the light. may this conversation be brought to the forefront. may this conversation no longer be had in secret. it is time
column3: for the truth to come to the light for all.

column1: don’t ignore what’s happening. being molested/raped/taken advantage of at a young age is mind-bending; life altering. it’s hard to imagine that these girl’s experiences didn’t get taken seriously. except for the fact that it didn’t and they weren’t. it’s harder to imagine that the reason behind the disbelief is because they are black. but... it was.

i read that the lgbtq (or back in 1988 when it officially formed: lgb) community specifically decided to put the “l” first in lbg because to be gay and a woman (2 minority groups) was incredibly difficult
column3: the “l” went first in the acronym.

this is the mindset we should adopt as well. no woman matters until all women matter. why that is now a revolution to so many is baffling... but as long as we get there in the end. so let’s start by changing our mindsets and perspectives to try and seek out these women - and just listen to them - to one another. hold each other up.

column1: i’ve loved @rayoandhoney’s banner she created a while back that said “no one is free until everyone is free”. so free yourself
column2: by raising up other women. especially the women who have minority upon minority stacked against them. race
column5: etc. those are the women and experiences that should hold the spotlight and without a doubt be taken seriously and with the utmost respect.

column1: and i just mentally want to thank my husband for always being supportive and willing to take a step back and listen. i’ve never experienced a more humble

column1: 76646;instagram;2019-01-14 21:14:42;FALSE;"[parte 2] entrevista com madeleine stowe para a gulf news tabloid!❤

stowe fala sobre a campanha que trouxe à tona abusos sexuais em hollywood e sua relação com o produtor harvey weinstein. além de também falar sobre como o seu contexto familiar influenciou seu trabalho filantrópico.
madeleine stowe participou de recentes movimentos sociais com atores de hollywood
column2: como a campanha #metoo que revelou abusos sexuais na indústria cinematográfica. o movimento começou a ganhar força quando várias atrizes falaram contra o magnata do cinema harvey weinstein.

column1: stowe trabalhou em vários filmes em que weinstein trabalhou como produtor executivo ou co-produtor
column2: como ""playing by heart"" (1998) e ""imposter"" (2001). “eu vou te contar uma historia engraçada. eu nunca tive um #metoo (quis dizer que nunca sofreu abuso sexual na indústria do cinema). eu fui uma das sortudas
column3: mas aparentemente isso [os abusos] ocorreu desenfreadamente
column4: tanto que fiquei chocada.” disse stowe. ""eu trabalhei com harvey e nunca tive nenhum problema porque ele sempre estava tentando me convencer a fazer um filme e eu não queria
column5: então era um equilíbrio de poder. mas nunca ninguém foi além de cortês comigo. e se você fosse a pessoa certa para um projeto
column7: e se não fosse – pra mim era muito negociável... mas são mulheres que não tem o poder de falar
column8: que tem que lidar com muito assédio no local de trabalho e isso é preocupante. é importante que o movimento do #metoo das atrizes não ofusque o que as mulheres reais estão passando”

column1: a atriz é um dos membros fundadores da apj
column2: e relembrou a criação de uma escola no haiti após o devastador terremoto em 2010
column3: e continua a trabalhar para o acesso à educação para jovens do mundo todo. “eu vim de um contexto muito difícil
column4: pessoalmente. e senti que tinha grande sorte dentro disso. nós tínhamos um sistema social na américa na época que permitia que você ficasse à tona...meu pai estava desesperadamente doente e minha mãe estava encarregada de cuidar dele e de três filhos porque ele não podia mais trabalhar. sinto como se tivesse tido sorte na vida ”

;[ pae 2 ] entrevista com madeleine stowe para gulf news tabloid ! ❤ stowe fala sobre campanha que trouxe à tona abusos sexuais em hollywood e sua relação com produtor harvey weinstein . além de sexuais na indústria cinematográfica . movimento começou ganhar força quando várias atrizes falaram contra magnata cinema harvey weinstein . stowe trabalhou em vários filmes em que weinstein trabalhou como produtor executivo ou co-produtor , como `` playing hea '' ( 1998 ) e `` imposter '' ( 2001 ) . “ eu vou te contar uma historia engraçada . eu nunca tive um ( quis dizer que nunca sofreu abuso sexual na indústria cinema ) . eu fui uma das soudas , mas aparentemente isso [ os abusos ] ocorreu desenfreadamente , tanto que fiquei chocada. ” disse stowe . `` eu trabalhei com harvey e nunca tive nenhum problema porque ele sempre estava tentando convencer fazer um filme e eu não queria , então era um equilíbrio de poder . mas nunca ninguém foi além de coês comigo . e se você fosse pessoa cea para um projeto , você era , e se não fosse – pra mim era muito negociável ... mas são mulheres que não tem poder de falar , que tem que lidar com muito assédio local de trabalho e isso é preocupante . é impoante que movimento das atrizes não ofusque que mulheres reais estão passando ” , diz stowe . atriz é um dos membros fundadores da apj , e relembrou criação de uma escola haiti após devastador column1: cleanliness: this toilet was clean with no stains and nothing that was fermenting within its crypts. the surrounding tile should have been cleaner. no spilled urine. 4/5🚻
tech/condition: this toilet has a self flushing systems that barely works. i had to press the button in order for it to flush
column2: but when flushing works very smoothly. wholesome sound
column3: not terribly loud after flush. there is a crack in the bottom of the base that seems worrying
column4: but the bowl is in good condition. surrounding tile is cracked and uneven 2/5🚻

column1: comfortability: there is no door in front of the toilet
column2: but there are stall walls. the walls are long enough for a sense of privacy
column3: but no door degrades that sense. the seat is cut in the front leaving for plenty of room and is at a nice height. 3/5🚻

column1: aesthetic: there is little aesthetic quality to this toilet and surrounding stall
column2: and i believe if it were not self flushing then that would add to the aesthetic. this toilet attempts a modern look but fails and looks beaten and scared. little effort. there are no messages or cryptic writings on the surroundimg walls
column3: and little color. although i will admit the tiles are pleasing to look at. boring. 2/5🚻

column1: this toilet works but would certainly not be my first recommendation. there is a much better
column2: newer option down the hall that sucks most competition. this toilet cetainly achieves its purpose
column3: but does not achieve anything further.

column1: i am terrified of my children growing up with a hypervigilant mother and an environment with a complete lack of boundaries. i am afraid of my identity becoming consumed in the successes and failures of my children. this is the way i was raised by a mother with severe childhood sexual trauma. for a long time
column2: i didn’t know where my mother ended and i began and i want better for my children. i want them to see models of healthy relationships in their home and break this chain.

column1: think about it for a second….
right now… is your life how you expected it to be 10 years ago?
now that’s not to say your life isn’t good
column2: or you cant be happy with where you are now…

column1: they change… you get unexpected curve balls thrown in.
but they will show up nonetheless.
am i saying … give up on the plans?
have the plans and the dreams but don’t get put off when things don’t go the way you expected them to in your head.
you cant play the movie out … not really

column1: 76737;instagram;2019-01-14 19:03:08;FALSE;"por favor sigam a minha página no instagram
(please follow my new page on instagram)
eu criei este projecto dedicado às mulheres e ao seu corpo
column2: e a opinião delas sobre o mundo da moda/redes sociais. este projecto é baseado em pequenas entrevistas
column3: com varias mulheres de diferentes raças
column4: onde elas falam sobre o seu corpo  e o impacto negativo das redes sociais nas suas vidas. através deste projecto eu percebi que as mulheres julgam a sua forma física a toda a hora e estão sempre preocupadas com o que os outros pensam sobre elas. como stylist
column5: eu quero produzir imagens de moda no futuro
column6: que façam com as mulheres se sintam melhores com elas próprias e os seus corpos.

column1: como é que te sentes em relação ao teu corpo?
as redes sociais tem um impacto na tua vida?
o que podemos mudar no mundo da moda no futuro?

column2: their bodies and their opinion about the fashion industry/social media.

column1: it is focusing on small interviews with many different women
column3: talking about their bodies and the negative impact on social media in their lives.

column2: i came to the conclusion that women are very self-conscious about their physical appearance and what others will think about the way they look.
i want to understand which kind of fashion imagery i can produce in the future
column3: to make women to feel better with themselves.

column1: how do you feel about your body?
what should change in the fashion industry in the future?

every single “battle wound” you have endured in your life are lines on your sleeve which show others that you are not defined by those experiences
my battle wound of sexual abuse as a child is a line on my sleeve.
my battle wound of being bullied as a child is a line on my sleeve.
my battle wound of suicidal thoughts as a teenager is a line on my sleeve.
my battle wound of failure in nursing school is a line on my sleeve.
my battle wound of financial debt is a line on my sleeve.
my battle wound of post partum depression and anxiety are a line on my sleeve.
my battle wound of business failure after business failure is a line on my sleeve.
our battle wounds do not define us
i am an online health mentor and trainer who teaches women how to overcome and be empowered by their scars rather than be defined by them.
workouts and nutrition alone won’t teach you the mental triggers and habits you need to achieve in order to master your body and mind!
that’s where i come in as a coach and with my virtual masterminds.
if you’ve been a woman being weighed down by your battle wounds
column2: let me be the one to help you this year to overcome and defeat!

column1: today is the very last day to launch into the new year with my actual tools and resources i’ve used to master and overcome my battle wounds in the last 4.5 years.

column2: then let’s do this girl! no more procrastinating and making excuses

column2: while also expressing regret for having worked with him in the past. the general public is now boycotting the singer’s music and so is his record label apparently. according to a report from tmz
column3: rca and sony are putting a hold on kelly’s music.

column1: kelly’s label is saying they will not produce
column3: or release any of his music until the allegations against him are resolved. there is currently a criminal investigation against the singer in georgia
column4: which is one of the major reasons why the label is wary of releasing any new music.

column1: tmz also reported that kelly has been in the studio writing and making new music and is upset at the fact that he has been frozen from releasing anything. in order to get out of his contract
column2: kelly must release two more albums
column3: but with the hold put on him
column4: he is unable to meet those requirements.

column1: i was 8 when i was sent to a mosque for my quran classes..the moulana there was a bit of an old man with gray hair and gray beard..i still feel anxiety building up inside me as i am writing this..he used to be a strict man but later few days his behaviour towards me grew a bit soft...it was mid summer when the classes were scheduled after fajr ..the class ended around 8 in the morning but the moulana instructed me to wait until all the kids left ..i was a small innocent kid tbh and din’t knew his intentions neither the reason behind his behaviour but as soon as the mosque was empty ..the moulana comes and holds my hand and kisses on it and then he holds me in his arms and starts humming all of a sudden i was freezed and couldn’t utter a word he touches me at the places where i felt really uncomfortable and scared..i wanted to stop him but his grip at me wrist was too tight and strong ..he leaves a smooch on my lips and starts touching me at places after few moments thankfully there was a cleaner climbing the stairs and suddenly this moulana moves away ..as soon as i got the chance i ran towards my house ..just the horror on my face was enough for my mother to sense the trouble..after few minutes of calming myself down i narrated this whole scene to my mom who was in tears by now..my mom then talked to my dad about this..but alas
column2: i was the one who was ordered to stay back at home and shut my mouth and never talk about this again with anyone since the status of this “moulana” was high enough in my society for people to even believe such incident...yet today i am 19 and the moulana still teaches the kids at the same mosque ..and i genuinely hope and pray that the kids there are safe and bold enough to defend themselves if anything happens ..

column1: this incident still gives me goosebumps whenever i happen to think about it ..i am speechless thinking that a even pure holy place isn’t safe as we think it is..may allah swt guide us all towards straight path and make us strong enough to fight back such people.

i was 8 when i was sent to a mosque for my quran classes..the moulana there was a bit of an old man with gray hair and gray beard..i still feel anxiety building up inside me as i am writing this..he used to be a strict man but later few days his behaviour towards me grew a bit soft...it was mid summer when the classes were scheduled after fajr ..the class ended around 8 in the morning but the moulana instructed me to wait until all the kids left ..i was a small innocent kid tbh and din’t knew his intentions neither the reason behind his behaviour but as soon as the mosque was empty ..the moulana comes and holds my hand and kisses on it and then he holds me in his arms and stas humming all of a sudden i was freezed and couldn’t utter a word he touches me at the places where i felt really uncomfoable and scared..i wanted to stop him but his grip at me wrist was too tight and strong ..he leaves a smooch on my lips and stas touching me at places after few moments thankfully there was a cleaner climbing the stairs and suddenly this moulana moves away ..as soon as i got the chance i ran towards my house ..just the horror on my face was enough for my mother to sense the trouble..after few minutes of calming myself down i narrated this whole scene to my mom who was in tears by now..my mom then talked to my dad about this..but alas

column1: 76881;instagram;2019-01-14 18:01:48;FALSE;"i am a survivor of sexual assault and an abusive relationship. and i am so proud of the woman i have become. it took time
column2: but i got the help needed and realized i had to start healing to live a healthy life. my healing journey began almost four years ago and it is far from over. i will be honest saying that it definitely has not been the easiest but it has been well worth it. i know that every survivor deserves peace and healing. it is attainable
column3: it is accessible and there are so many people who want to help you. you are not alone. and you do not have to carry this pain alone. no one is deserving of an abusive relationship. it’s not fair to have experienced these things
column4: however it is in your control to make a change and help yourself! ❤️❤️❤️ @mentalhealthamerica

column1: 76955;instagram;2019-01-14 16:59:10;FALSE;"modesty is a heart posture not a closet choice! im going to say something that the saints are gonna screenshot but i’m here to break even christian cultural chains! 😇“modesty” must be one of the most abused words in the christianese lexicon.
the idea of modesty has been almost exclusively attached to women’s dress
column2: narrowing in definition to mean “showing less skin and trying to prevent sexual arousal in those looking on.” the idea of femininity and faith rarely coexist in black christianity because of the patriarchal and sexist underpinnings. as a black community we work hard to cover (google john gray) and protect our men. so much so that we as women claim responsibility over their sexual arrousal. (google rkelly) instead of teaching our young boys to respect and honor women
column3: we tell our girls to tuck away and hide behind sackcloth! its literally insane.

column1: modesty like the messiah should be the aim
column2: jesus didn’t make a fuss over his clothes and what people thought about him
column3: and neither should we. what we wear should not define who we are and whose we are. modesty in dress is a subset of modesty that needs to be addressed. both paul and peter instruct women to not be superfluous in their dress so that no adornment outshines the act of modesty. as long as your dress does not outshine your heart

column1: unfortunately this idea of homiliness in order to gain holiness has shifted our culture in such a way that personal style and creatively
column2: celebrating who god created you to be is viewed as radical and out of line.

column1: a lot of rules and “religiosity” regulations around modesty have been justified as “protecting” the woman from onlookers
column3: and judgement from the community. when in reality we are perpetuating the same behavior that the current #metoo and #timesups movements are trying to destroy.

column1: because the enemy walks amongst us here on earth
column2: he uses what we see to find ways for us to persecute each other! if we could see the hearts of men like god
column3: would what they wear really matter so much?

column3: welcome! the #hikingmyfeelings speaking + hiking tour explores the mind-body connection that i (@sydneyunfiltered) found on the #transcatalinatrail. i connect the dots between a sexual assault i survived 12+ years ago and my diabetes diagnosis
column4: and all the changes in my life since i started managing this disease. i was able to recreate myself outside
column5: reclaim parts of my body and dignity that were stolen from me during the assault
column6: and rebuild a life out of the ashes when it all came crashing down in early 2018. don't forget
column7: we have group hikes tied to each of these speaking stops so let's talk it out on friday night and walk it out on saturday! and if you're curious about #vanlife
column8: ruby (our van) will be available for tours before and after the speaking + hiking events!

column3: you'll be ready to thru-hike across catalina island in no time! of course

column5: everyone is welcome! 💚💚💚 see you on the road and on the trail!

column1: 76985;instagram;2019-01-14 16:28:47;FALSE;"what can we do to help you?
you may be asking yourself this question.
recently we were contacted by a woman on the brink of quitting her job due to the severity of abuse she was experiencing at the hands of her colleagues.
after contacting managers and supervisors and seeing no change
column2: whistle blowers association were able to get in contact with senior managers within the organisation she worked for. all whilst maintaining her anonymity.
the harassment ceased due to the organisation proactively addressing every department in the company.
if you are feeling nervous to report your case to us
column3: don’t be. you’re most likely not the only one experiencing the abuse
column4: and we will always maintain your identity anonymous.

column1: don’t forget to follow us and fill in the survey in our site!
contact us directly or through michaelantonrouse@gmail.com
